    <!--
      Gradient color palettes — 100-step sequential colormaps.

      Intended use: SQL filters that bucket tracks into exactly 100 histogram
      groups (0–99). The group label produced by the SQL must be the numeric
      bucket index (as a string) in ascending order so that getColorForGroup()
      assigns colors[0] → bucket 0, colors[1] → bucket 1, etc.

      Example SQL pattern:
        NTILE(100) OVER (ORDER BY avg_speed_kmh) - 1   AS color_group

      Palettes:
        GRADIENT_100_VIRIDIS  — perceptually uniform, colorblind-safe (default)
        GRADIENT_100_PLASMA   — warm/energetic, good for effort/heat metrics
        GRADIENT_100_BLUES    — single-hue, quiet on the eye
        GRADIENT_100_RDYLGN   — red (low) → yellow → green (high), intuitive for speed/performance
    -->

